article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 65, Webber 61
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Tobias Mahone hit four free throws and Stanley Elliott added another in the final 19 seconds to preserve Bethune-Cookman's 65-61 victory over Webber International on Tuesday night. The Wildcats (3-4) trailed most of the game, but took a 55-53 lead on two free throws by Alexander Starling with 3:02 to play. Two more Starling free throws gave Bethune-Cookman a 60-55 lead with 31.5 seconds left, but Brandon Streeter's 3-pointer cut the margin to 60-58 seven seconds later. After Mahone made two free throws, Webber's Tyler Hoevanaar hit a 3-pointer for 62-61 with 3.8 seconds left. Free throws by Elliott and Mahone sealed the win. Starling scored 18 points for Bethune-Cookman, while C.J. Reed added 14 and John Holmes 12. Halston Schaffer scored 13 points to lead the Warriors (4-3) and Streeter and Tyrell Harper netted 12 points apiece.
